        "content": "# LAB-4.3 \u2014 Threat Hunting Workflow (ELK): Hypothesis \u2192 Query \u2192 Validate \u2192 Report\n\n**Case:** CJ-013  \n**Campaign:** Cinder Jackal vs ApexFin Solutions  \n**Date:** 2025-09-02  \n**ATT&CK:** T1087\n\n## Analyst narrative\nStudents convert hypotheses into Elastic queries, validate results against case evidence, and decide what should be promoted into MISP as actionable CTI.\n\n## CTI promotion guidance\n- Promote only validated observables from TheHive/Cortex into this MISP event.\n- Keep `to_ids=false` for baseline infrastructure, documentation ranges, internal IPs, and workflow metadata.\n- Keep `to_ids=true` for behaviorally useful detection indicators such as malicious command lines, staged payload names, suspicious URLs, named pipes, and fictional campaign IOCs.\n- Add sightings during the lab when the same observable appears in Elastic/Wazuh/Zeek queries.\n\n## Source artifacts\n- schtask_modification_2020-12-1907505969.json\n- empire_schtasks_creation_standard_user_2020-09-21031526.json\n",
